[SN]TITLE[SN]
Burton Albion 1-0 Swindon Town

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Substitute Lucas Akins scored a late penalty to beat Swindon and ensure Burton Albion ended 2015 in the League One automatic promotion places.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Mark Duffy, Nasser El Khayati and Stuart Beavon were all denied by Swindon keeper Lawrence Vigouroux.
At the other end, Jon McLaughlin produced a stunning save to keep out Jonathan Obika's point-blank volley.
Akins scored from the spot after Jordan Turnbull had tripped Beavon as Burton end the year in second place.
Burton Albion manager Nigel Clough told BBC Radio Derby:
